---
description: FastAPI backend rules
globs: backend/**, api/**, app/**.py
---

Backend stack:
- Python 3.12
- FastAPI, Uvicorn
- Pydantic, SQLAlchemy 2.0, Alembic
- PostgreSQL 16 for persistence
- Redis 7 for cache, rate limiting, and Celery broker
- Celery for async video and moderation tasks
- OpenAI GPT-4o / GPT-4o-mini (vision + text), Whisper, LangChain 0.2+, LangGraph
- FFmpeg, OpenCV, PyAV for video processing
- AWS S3 for video, thumbnails, and artifacts
- Pinecone for vector store (similarity search, embeddings)
- WebSockets for real-time live stream status and moderation alerts
- AWS SQS for durable async pipelines where required

Backend rules:
- Use clean architecture.
- Routes/controllers should only handle HTTP/WebSocket concerns.
- Business logic must live in services (video, moderation, analytics, storage, stream).
- Database access must live in repositories.
- Validation must be done using Pydantic schemas/models.
- Use dependency injection patterns where appropriate.
- Use async I/O for external calls (OpenAI, S3, Pinecone, DB).
- Use pagination for list endpoints (videos, moderation queue, alerts).
- Use consistent response models and error envelope `{ error: { code, message, details } }`.
- Support WebSocket endpoints for live stream and moderation updates per API_SPEC.md.

Preferred backend structure (per CLAUDE.md):
- app/api/v1/          (auth, videos, moderation, analytics, live, policies, webhooks)
- app/models/          (user, video, moderation, policy, analytics, alert)
- app/schemas/
- app/services/        (auth, video, moderation, analytics, storage, notification, stream)
- app/ai/agents/       (orchestrator, content_analyzer, safety_checker, metadata_extractor, scene_classifier, report_generator)
- app/ai/chains/       (moderation_chain, insight_chain, summary_chain)
- app/ai/graphs/       (video_analysis_graph, moderation_workflow)
- app/ai/tools/        (frame_extractor, audio_transcriber, ocr_tool, object_detector, similarity_search)
- app/ai/prompts/
- app/workers/         (celery_app, video_tasks, moderation_tasks, analytics_tasks, cleanup_tasks)
- app/core/            (security, exceptions, middleware, logging)
- app/utils/

Coding expectations:
- Add type hints to functions.
- Add docstrings for non-trivial service methods.
- Keep routes thin and declarative.
- Keep service methods focused and testable.
- Reuse existing utilities before creating new ones.
- Isolate video processing and AI agent logic behind clear interfaces.

Do not:
- Put SQL or ORM-heavy logic inside route files.
- Put business logic inside Pydantic schemas.
- Put environment variables directly across many files; centralize config.
- Mix unrelated domains in the same service file.
- Hardcode OpenAI keys, S3 credentials, or DB URLs; use config/env.
